        <graphic xlink:href="pone.0123658.g003"/>
      </fig>
      <p>To see why mBeta t-test method had so high efficiency and stability, we used plot of log fold change against <italic>t</italic>-value to compare Beta <italic>t</italic>-test to mBeta <italic>t</italic>-test (see <xref rid="pone.0123658.g004" ref-type="fig">Fig 4</xref>). In Beta <italic>t</italic>-test, <italic>t</italic>-value distributes from -16 to 16, while in mBeta <italic>t</italic>-test, <italic>t</italic>-value distributes from -70 to 120. On the other hand, <xref rid="pone.0123658.g004" ref-type="fig">Fig 4</xref> shows that Beta <italic>t</italic>-test has acceptable region of -4 to 4 and many false discoveries scattered in two rejection regions nearby acceptable region while mBeta <italic>t</italic>-test significantly compresses acceptable region to a very narrow interval close to zero such that the false discoveries (blue dots) are significantly reduced.</p>
      <fig id="pone.0123658.g004" orientation="portrait" position="float">
