          <p><italic>t</italic>-values were obtained by the two Beta <italic>t</italic>-test methods from the simulated data in which values τ = 100<italic>U</italic> were assigned to 10% of genes for differential expression between two given conditions each with three replicates. LogFC on y-axis represents log fold change in expression. In the Beta t-test method (A), <italic>t</italic>-value was distributed in the interval between -16 and 16 and acceptable region for non-differential expression was spanned from -4.0 to 4.0. Many false positives (blue dots) were found in two rejection areas. But in the mBeta t-test method (B), the interval for t-values was enlarged to span from -70 to 120 and the acceptable region for non-differential expression was strongly compressed into a narrow interval close to zero so that few false positives (blue dots) were found in rejection areas.</p>
